bioghist.head: Historical note
bioghist.p: The Executive Vice President and Treasurer writes the yearly budget report for the Board of Trustees.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: The material in this collection includes brochures, forms, ledger books, microfilm, budget reports, scrapbooks, awards, estate and gift files, financial records, financial reports, president's reports, framed photographs, and memorabilia. These records date from 1903 to 2010. Not all of the series are processed. Please see staff for assistance.

arrangement.head: Collection Organization
arrangement.p: Organized into eighteen series: Brochures, Financial records, Financial records, Financial records, Awards, Estate records, Financial records, Scrapbooks, Office files, Office files, Financial records, Financial records, three titled Sponsored Research projects, Office files, Certificates, and Reports, photographs, and memorabilia.

did.abstract: This book includes reciepts for cash payments recieved by the University from April 29, 1963 - January 17, 1965. Receipts signed by the University Treasurer. Includes information on stock dividends and loose paper reciepts from other transactions. Good Condition. Loose receipts are kept within pages as well as some delicately glued on receipts, so please turn pages delicately.

did.unittitle: University Loan Record | The George Washington University 1937 - 1949 Book #1
did.abstract: Includes a name by name record of the university's student loans disbursements, amounts owed on balances, recapitulations, and outstanding loan balances. Rcords of 3,478 loan disbursements over 13 years recorded.
did.physdesc: Small ledger book. Measures 8.5" x 10". Good condition. Dark fabric cover with red leather corners and spine.

did.unittitle: University Loan Record | The George Washington University 1950 - 1959 Book #2
did.abstract: Includes a name by name record of the university's student loans disbursements, recapitulations, and outstanding loan balances from September 8, 1950 - October 14, 1959. By 1957, records become generalized for the toal amounts recieved for specific sessions.
did.physdesc: Small ledger book. Measures 10" x 8.5". Very Good Condition. Dark fabric cover with red leather corners and spine. Shows some signs of wear.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents note
scopecontent.p: This series contains correspondence, receipts, brochures, proposals, reports, press releases, biographic information, a questionnaire, reports, memorandums, guides, and an invitation. They range in date from 1820 to 2003. The materials concern real estate transactions; student loans; services; planning; physical facilities; budgets; endowments; annual reports; the Fiscal Planning and Budgeting Committee, the Information Systems and Services (ISS); the Computer Information and Resource Center (CIRC); the Advisory Council on Academic Computing; the Center for Academic and Administrative Computing; Information Technology Services; and technology. Materials also concern Henry W. Herzog, formerly University Vice President and Treasurer.
Formerly vertical files

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: This box contains framed photographs of GW campus scenes. The photographs formerly hung in the hallway of the Rice Hall offfice of the Executive Vice President and Treasurer. Subjects include:

1. Students reading on a bench. 2. Men in front of a ribbon, balloons in the background. 3. Asian dancers in yellow costumes with red fans. 4. Volleyball game, blue seats in background, ball in upper left. 5. Man standing above construction site. 6. Boys in a decorated car, driving through the city to a game. 7. Students standing in front of a solar car. 8. 2000 Pennsylvania Avenue lit up at night. 9. Naval officer commissioning. 10. Fountain/garden area.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents

11. Graduates celebrating, May 1993. 12. Students set up living area in front of Professor's Gate. 13. Baseball: Base coach, runner & baseman action shot. 14. Basketball: GW vs. Mississippi State, two players at net. 15. GW Women's crew team racing (yellow boat). 16. Indian girl in red dress, blurry tulips in foreground. 17.
